OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FOpium production in Myanmar
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fsurges to nine-year high   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The production of opium increased      
OL,6, sharply in Myanmar after falling for   
OL,7, seven years, according to the UN.      
OL,9,FIt touched nearly 795 metric tonnes in 
OL,10,F2022, nearly double the production in  
OL,11,F2021 - 423 metric tonnes - the year of 
OL,12,Fthe military coup.                     
OL,14,FThe UN believes this is driven by      
OL,15,Feconomic hardship and insecurity, along
OL,16,Fwith higher global prices for the opium
OL,17,Fresin that is used to make heroin.     
OL,19,FThe coup plunged much of Myanmar into a
OL,20,Fbloody civil war that still continues. 
